Subject: [PATCH] Add P2 QA artifacts: E2E strategy, coverage report, evidence
 and risk register

### Motivation
- Establish a realistic P2 production QA baseline and formalize an E2E strategy without introducing new product features or risky infra changes.
- Capture current test posture, critical flows and known blockers for adding coverage and browser E2E so future phases can proceed with a clear plan.

### Description
- Add `.ops/p2-e2e-coverage-production-qa/e2e-strategy.md` documenting critical flows, scope (Vitest integration-first), onboarding/session strategy and Playwright deferral rationale.
- Add `.ops/p2-e2e-coverage-production-qa/evidence.md` recording the setup found, actions performed and the real command results.
- Add `.ops/p2-e2e-coverage-production-qa/coverage-report.md` explaining the attempted coverage flow and the blocker around `@vitest/coverage-v8`, and add `.ops/p2-e2e-coverage-production-qa/qa-risk-register.md` cataloguing QA risks and next actions.
- No runtime code, tests or Supabase schema/migrations were changed and no new dependencies were permanently added.

### Testing
- Ran `npm run lint` and `npm run typecheck`, both completed successfully.
- Ran `npm test` (Vitest) and `140 files / 534 tests` passed.
- Ran `npm run build` successfully.
- Attempted coverage with `npx vitest run --coverage` which failed due to a missing coverage provider (`@vitest/coverage-v8`) and the subsequent `npm i -D @vitest/coverage-v8` failed with a registry policy `403`, so coverage integration was deferred and documented in the artifacts.
